#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp.docbook:55
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The similarity between the two products means that much day-to-day data "
#| "can be imported in a straightforward fashion. However, there are some "
#| "areas where differences arise, and various options are provided to deal "
#| "with these. The following sections will describe some of these "
#| "differences; understanding them should lead to a smoother importation."
msgid ""
"The similarity between the two products means that much day-to-day data can "
"be imported in a straightforward fashion. However, there are some areas "
"where there are differences, and various options are provided to deal with "
"these. The following sections will describe some of these differences; "
"understanding them should lead to a smoother import, where any of them are "
"relevant to your data."
msgstr ""
"Sličnost između dva proizvoda znači da se većina sadašnjih podataka može "
"unijeti direktno. Ipak, postoje područja u kojima se pojavljuju "
"razlitičosti, i mnoštvo opcija je pruženo kako ne bi došlo do problema. "
"Sljedeći odlomak će opisati neke od tih razlika; razumijevanje istih bi "
"trebalo olakšati unos."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Similarities, Differences, and Terminology"
msgstr "Sličnosti, razlike i terminologija"

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Small Business Usage"
msgstr "Upotreba malih preduzeća"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp.docbook:67
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "It should be noted that &kappname; is a <emphasis>personal</emphasis> "
#| "finance manager, and as such, does not directly support any of the "
#| "business features of GnuCash, such as tax tables, payroll, and tracking "
#| "of lots. Any Accounts Payable or Receivable accounts found in a file will "
#| "be imported as Liability or Asset accounts respectively."
msgid ""
"It should be noted that &kmymoney; is a <emphasis>personal</emphasis> "
"finance manager, and as such, does not directly support any of the business "
"features of &gnucash;, such as tax tables, payroll, and tracking of lots. "
"Any Accounts Payable or Receivable accounts found in a file will be imported "
"as Liability or Asset accounts respectively."
msgstr ""
"Treba napomenuti da je &kappname; <emphasis>osobni</emphasis> finansijski "
"menadžer i kao takav, ne podržava direktno GnuCash osobine, kao što su "
"tabele poreza, platni spisak i praćenje parcela. Bilo koji račun, sa kojeg "
"se može plaćati ili koji može primati novac, koji se nalazi u datoteci će "
"biti unesen kao Liability ili Asset račun respektivno."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accounts"
msgstr "Računi"

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Account types"
msgstr "Tipovi računa"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp.docbook:79
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "For both products, the highest level of structure in the file is the "
#| "account. &kappname; supports 5 main types of account: Asset, Liability, "
#| "Income, Expense and Equity, each of which may have various subtypes, "
#| "&eg;, Checking, Credit Card, &etc; &kappname; includes a 'standard' "
#| "account for each of these five types, and all other accounts are held "
#| "subordinate to one of these. &kappname; enforces more consistency (or "
#| "less flexibility, depending on your point of view) between account types "
#| "than does GnuCash, and the importer will correct any inconsistencies it "
#| "detects. This may result in a slightly different account structure, "
#| "though this can, within reason, be amended after the import is complete."
msgid ""
"For both products, the highest level of structure in the file is the "
"account. &kmymoney; supports 5 main types of account: Asset, Liability, "
"Income, Expense, and Equity, each of which may have various subtypes, &eg;, "
"Checking, Credit Card, &etc; &kmymoney; includes a 'standard' account for "
"each of these five types, and all other accounts are held subordinate to one "
"of these. &kmymoney; enforces more consistency (or less flexibility, "
"depending on your point of view) between account types than does &gnucash;, "
"and the importer will correct any inconsistencies it detects. This may "
"result in a slightly different account structure, though this can, within "
"reason, be amended after the import is complete."
msgstr ""
"Za oba proizvoda, najviši nivo strukture u datoteci je račun. &kappname; "
"podržava 5 glavnih tipova računa: Asset, Liability, Income, Expense i "
"Equity, od kojih svaki može imati podtipove, &eg;, Checking, Credit Card, "
"&etc; &kappname; uključuje 'standardni' račun za svaki od ovih pet tipova i "
"svi ostali računi se čuvaju kao podređeni ovima. &kappname; podstiče veću "
"dosljednost (ili manju fleksibilnost, u ovisnosti od vaše tačke posmatranja) "
"između tipova računa nego GnuCash, i importer će prepraviti sve "
"nedosljednosti koje prepozna. Ovo može rezultovati sa blago promijenjenom "
"strukturom računa, međutim ukoliko je potrebno, to se može prepraviti nakon "
"što je unos završen."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "Categories"
msgstr "Kategorije"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp.docbook:93
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kappname; uses the term Category to denote an account of an Income or "
#| "Expense type. Unlike GnuCash, these are not considered as 'ledger' "
#| "accounts, and entry of transactions folder into categories is not "
#| "supported; allocations are made during transaction entry into other "
#| "account types."
msgid ""
"&kmymoney; uses the term Category to denote an account of an Income or "
"Expense type. Unlike &gnucash;, these are not considered as <quote>ledger</"
"quote> accounts, and entry of transactions directly into categories is not "
"supported. Allocations to Categories are made when transactions are entered "
"or edited in other account types."
msgstr ""
"&kappname; koristi termin Kategorije da obilježi račune Income i Expense "
"tipa. Za razliku od GnuCash-a, oni se ne smatraju kao 'ledger'(glavni) "
"računi i unos foldera transakcija u kategorije nije podržano; alokacije se "
"vrše u druge tipove računa prilikom unosa transakcije."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Structure and Placeholders"
msgstr "Struktura i Placeholders (držači mjesta)"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp.docbook:103
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "GnuCash supports the use of Placeholder accounts. In effect, these are "
#| "just read-only accounts into which no transactions can be entered, but "
#| "which function in an analogous fashion to folders in a folder structure, "
#| "as a holder for other accounts. Though &kappname; does not support this "
#| "feature as such, it does provide a parent/child account relationship, so "
#| "the importer simulates placeholders by creating empty accounts."
msgid ""
"&gnucash; supports the use of Placeholder accounts. In effect, these are "
"just read-only accounts into which no transactions can be entered, but which "
"function in an analogous fashion to folders in a folder structure, as a "
"holder for other accounts. Though &kmymoney; does not support this feature "
"as such, it does provide a parent/child account relationship, so the "
"importer simulates placeholders by creating empty accounts."
msgstr ""
"GnuCash podržava upotrebu Placeholder računa. Ovo su samo za čitanje računi "
"u koje se ne mogu unijeti transakcije, ali koji se ponašaju analogno kao "
"folderi iz strukture foldera, predstavljaju držače za ostale račune. Iako "
"&kappname; ne podržava ovu osobinu takvu kakva jeste, on pruža roditelj/"
"dijete odnos između računa, tako da importer simulira placeholdere "
"pravljenjem praznih računa."

